    "body": "**Software and hardware versions**\r\nAll Android devices\r\n\r\n**Problem description**\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/85225519/181047482-671b1e81-d8a6-4db8-962d-fae7785ad7bf.mp4\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce:**\r\n\r\n1. Go to Project Settings -> Maps and Select any map as Source;\r\n2. Open form with select map e.g. [map-internal-select-advanced.xlsx](https://github.com/getodk/collect/files/9191160/map-internal-select-advanced.xlsx)\r\n3. Click on \"Select Place\" button and select any point on map;\r\n4. Click on \"Select Place\" button again and click on Crosshair button;\r\n5. Rotate the screen;\r\n6. User is taken back to the selected point.\r\n  \r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\n- User should not be moved from his location to the selected point location after rotating the screen\r\n\r\n",
